== Two-year DC2 plan (April 2027 -- March 2029)

- *Year 1.* Pillar 1 --- formal coupling bounds; validation on IEEE 14/30/57/118; submission to IEEE Trans. Smart Grid; conference paper at IEEE ICC or GLOBECOM.
- *Year 2.* Pillars 2 and 3 --- multi-impairment extension on PEGASE 2,869-bus; SLM-based SCADA on real PMU data; submissions to /Applied Energy/ and IEEE Trans. Power Systems; dissertation finalisation.

== Impact and outlook

The doctoral work bridges three traditionally separate communities --- power-system control theory, deep learning, and grid cybersecurity --- and is intended to seed a *Japan / Côte d'Ivoire research bridge* on smart-grid resilience for emerging-economy grids.

For the full publication record, see [publications.html publications].
